<br>
I do agree, however, that would be extremely hard to regulate, and would hate to deal with the griefers, or people who are just there to PK for no real reason.  I do think either some zones should be PvP enabled, or some actions give you a timed PvP flag.<br>
<br>
For instance, evil's killing guards in Felwithe would make them PvP enabled, so that HIE's could &quot;assist in the defense&quot; of Felwithe, for instance.  I hate the fact that RP is jeopardized because of the griefer, or powergamer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gemlin>Gemlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/03 11:09:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25419.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sam DeathWalker RoXoRs yur BoXoRs!</span><hr size=1> Play on a Zek then. They have Good Vs Evil There. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=554190">Gemlin - 65 Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
