<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You can't really add PvP-only content at this stage without pissing off a bunch of people.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It might show the bloobies that there is something more than just their normal PvE routine, and if they bitch, then they're just bitching to bitch.<br>
The devs are constantly adding in stuff that the majority of the players aren't interested in, but they generally don't bitch. Sure, some might, but those are the people that bitch because they always bitch.<br>
<br>
Consider that PoP is the top of the ladder; what are all those level 65, AA maxed players going to do when they've gotten to PoTime and saved Zeb? They're probably going to quit or play an alt. They can't really raise the level cap anymore without ruining PoP. They can add more AA, but after you've &quot;beaten&quot; the toughest zone(s) that can be in the game, what else is there to do?<br>
<br>
Refining the PvP rules across all servers might be an incentive for them to stay playing, which would continue to bring in money for Sony. Afterall, that's what this is all about; giving players a reason to continue paying their $12 a month so EQ can continue running.<br>
